{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Wasabi mayonnaise","content":["Place a jug onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh grapeseed oil into it. Set jug aside.","Place egg yolks, mustard, lemon juice and salt into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Mix <nobr>2 min\/speed 4<\/nobr>, slowly pouring oil onto mixing bowl lid, letting it drizzle into mixing bowl to emulsify.","Add wasabi and mix <nobr>4 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Transfer mayonnaise into a sealable jar or container and place into refrigerator until use. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Asian crab cakes","content":["Place lime zest into mixing bowl and grate <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then repeat grating <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula again.","Add spring onions\/shallots and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add crab meat, soy sauce, 2 of the eggs, 80 g of the breadcrumbs and 60 g of the reserved wasabi mayonnaise and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer mixture into a bowl, cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator to chill (approx. 1 hour). Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place flour, salt and pepper into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer seasoned flour into a bowl and set aside.","Place remaining 2 eggs into a ceramic or glass bowl and lightly beat to create an egg wash. Set egg wash aside.","Place a separate ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh sesame seeds and remaining 20 g breadcrumbs into it. Stir gently to combine.","Remove chilled crab mixture from refrigerator, then take 2 teaspoons of the mixture and form into a small ball (approx. 4 cm in diameter). Dip ball into the seasoned flour, then flatten slightly to form a crab cake shape. Dip crab cake into egg wash, then roll in reserved sesame seed-breadcrumb mixture. Repeat process until all chilled crab mixture has been used to form approx. 14 crab cakes.","Place a medium-sized non-stick frying pan over a medium-high heat and add vegetable oil. Place crab cakes into frying pan and fry on both sides until golden brown and cooked through (approx. 4 minutes). Transfer onto a plate lined with paper towel to blot excess oil.","Place crab cakes onto a platter, top with Japanese pickled ginger and serve with extra wasabi mayonnaise on the side."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Wasabi mayonnaise","content":["250 g grapeseed oil","2 egg yolks","2 tsp Dijon mustard","1 tsp lemon juice","1 pinch fine salt, to taste","25 g wasabi paste, to taste"]},{"title":"Asian crab cakes","content":["½ lime, zest only, no white pith","2 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into quarters (approx. 40 g)","250 g fresh crab meat","2 tbsp soy sauce","4 eggs","100 g breadcrumbs, plus extra for coating","70 g plain flour","1 - 2 pinches sea salt, to taste","1 - 2 pinches ground black pepper, to taste","50 g white sesame seeds","2 tbsp vegetable oil","Japanese pickled ginger, to serve"]}],"id":"r90082","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-g6X9LVoQoVc\/XZMvQRUJ4GI\/AAAAAAAAaPg\/cmrf4S2WpHEP_uLQqiVySzrwy1VWIq5VACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_bGV7jV2a6mb9djY6.png","title":"Asian crab cakes with wasabi mayonnaise","publishedAt":"2015-12-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.6 g","fat":"22 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"10 g","calories":"1110 kJ \/ 264 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large jug, sealable storage jar or container, plastic wrap, ceramic or glass bowl, paper towel, turner \/ fish slice, medium-sized non-stick frying pan, refrigerator, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["To prepare ahead of time, make crab cakes as per recipe up to the end of step 13. Allow fried crab cakes to cool to room temperature, then transfer into a freezable container and place into the freezer to store for up to 6 weeks. Bake crab cakes in the oven until heated through, then prepare a fresh quantity of wasabi mayonnaise just before serving.","You can substitute the crab meat with prawn flesh if you prefer."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 30m","14 pieces"]}